{{Infobox protected area | name = Coso Range Wilderness | iucn_category = | map = USA | relief = 1 | map_caption = | location = [[Inyo County, California|Inyo County]], [[California]], [[United States|USA]] | coordinates = {{coords|36.265794|N|117.850474|W|display=inline, title}}<ref name="blm"/> | area = {{convert|49,296|acre|0}} | established = 1994 | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | governing_body = [[Bureau of Land Management]] }}
The '''Coso Range Wilderness''' is a protected [[wilderness area]] in [[California]] in the northern end of the [[Coso Range]].<ref name="wilderness connect">{{cite web |url=https://www.wilderness.net/NWPS/wildView?WID=136&tab=General |title=Coso Range Wilderness |website=Wilderness connect |access-date=August 10, 2018}}</ref>
The area was designated as wilderness by the [[California Desert Protection Act of 1994]]<ref name="govtrack">{{cite web |url=https://www.govtrack.us/congress/bills/103/s21/text |access-date=August 10, 2018 |title=S. 21 (103rd): California Desert Protection Act of 1994. |website=govTrack}}</ref> and contains [[Yucca brevifolia|Joshua trees]], creosote, and cactus as well as old mining areas.<ref name="blm">{{cite web |url=https://www.blm.gov/visit/coso-range-wilderness |access-date=August 10, 2018 |title=Coso Range Wilderness |website=[[Bureau of Land Management]]}}</ref> ==References== {{reflist}}
