{{Orphan|date=June 2011}}

'''East Scotia Basin''' is a [[oceanic basin|submarine basin]] that lies in the [[Scotia Sea]] of the [[South Atlantic]] ocean, behind the [[South Sandwich Trench|South Sandwich trench]] and between [[latitude]]s 55&ndash;60°&nbsp;S. It is bounded to the north by the North Scotia Ridge, which includes the island of [[South Georgia Island|South Georgia]], and to the east by the [[South Sandwich Islands]]. A rise that runs from South Georgia to the [[South Orkney Islands]] separates the East Scotia Basin from the [[West Scotia Basin]].<ref name=christie2006/><ref name=pce8/>

