'''Geoffrey Bannister''' (born 1946, [[Manchester, England]]<ref name=star/>) was  an [[England|English]]-[[United States|American]] [[education|educator]] and [[geographer]]. He is the fourth president of [[Hawai'i Pacific University]]. His goals for the [[university]] were to expand the [[graduate program]] [[research]] as well as building connections with other universities around the world.<ref name=star>http://www.staradvertiser.com/columnists/20110225_Geoffrey_Bannister.html?id=116897758</ref>
<ref>http://www.hawaiibusiness.com/Hawaii-Business/May-2011/Geoffrey-Bannister/</ref>

Bannister was born in Manchester, England. When he was 10 years old, his family moved to [[New Zealand]]. He later moved to [[Toronto]], [[Canada]] to get [[doctorate]] in [[geography]]. He became a U.S. [[citizen]] in 1989.<ref name=star/>

