{{Other uses2|Grenadine}} {{Infobox settlement <!--See Template:Infobox Settlement for additional fields that may be available--> <!--See the Table at Infobox Settlement for all fields and descriptions of usage--> <!-- Basic info ----------------> |official_name = Grenadine Islands |nickname = <!-- images and maps -----------> |image_map =Grenadines.svg |right |mapsize = 250px |map_caption = Location within the Grenadines. <!-- Location ------------------> |coordinates = |subdivision_type = [[Region]] |subdivision_name = [[Caribbean]] |subdivision_type1 = [[Island country|Island States]] |subdivision_name1 = {{Collapsible list | title = 2 | {{GRD}} | {{Flag|Saint Vincent and the Grenadines }} }} | admin_center_type = | settlement_type = [[Caribbean|Region of the Caribbean]] <!-- Area ---------------------> |area_magnitude = |unit_pref = <!--Enter: Imperial, if Imperial (metric) is desired--> |area_footnotes = |area_total_km2 = 86 |area_total_sq_mi = <!-- Population -----------------------> |population_as_of = |population_footnotes = |population_note = |population_total = est. 20,880 | population_density_km2 = 194.2 | population_demonym = <!-- General information ---------------> |timezone = [[Atlantic Standard Time Zone|AST]] |utc_offset = −5 |timezone_DST = ADT |utc_offset_DST = −4 <!-- Area/postal codes & others --------> |postal_code_type = |postal_code = |area_code = }}
The '''Grenadines''' are a chain of small islands that lie on a line between the larger islands of [[Saint Vincent (Antilles)|Saint Vincent]] and [[Grenada]] in the [[Lesser Antilles]]. The northern two-thirds of the chain, including about 32 islands and cays, are part of the country of [[Saint Vincent and the Grenadines]]. Nine are inhabited, including the mainland Saint Vincent and the Grenadines islands: Young Island, Bequia, Mustique, Canouan, Union Island, Mayreau, Petit St Vincent, and Palm Island. The southern third of the chain belongs to the country of [[Grenada]]. [[Carriacou]] is the largest And most populated (excluding Grenada)
==Geographic boundaries== They are divided between the [[island nations]] of [[Saint Vincent and the Grenadines]] and [[Grenada]]. They lie between the islands of [[Saint Vincent (island)|Saint Vincent]] in the north and Grenada in the south. Neither Saint Vincent nor Grenada are Grenadine islands. The islands north of the [[Martinique Channel]] belong to Saint Vincent and the Grenadines and the islands south of the channel belong to Grenada.
