[[File:Bi Luochun.jpg|thumb|[[Green tea]] cultivation in China]]
This is a '''list of Chinese teas'''. [[Chinese tea]] is a beverage made from the leaves of [[tea]] plants (''[[Camellia sinensis]]'') and – depending on the type of tea – typically 60–100&nbsp;°C hot water. Tea leaves are processed using traditional Chinese methods. Chinese tea is drunk throughout the day, including during meals, as a substitute for plain water, for health, or for simple pleasure.
